WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:11.136 --> 00:00:13.346
-[sirens blaring]
-[dramatic music playing]

2
00:00:18.685 --> 00:00:21.563
[man speaking]

3
00:00:23.000 --> 00:00:29.074
Tired of searching for subtitles?
Ray generates them instantly: getray.app

4
00:00:34.868 --> 00:00:38.079
[woman speaking]

5
00:00:49.090 --> 00:00:50.884
[man] I'm thinking to myself.

6
00:00:50.967 --> 00:00:55.513
this is just
the most outrageous story I've heard

7
00:00:55.597 --> 00:00:57.766
in all of my years as a detective.

8
00:00:58.391 --> 00:01:00.268
[man speaking]

9
00:01:03.688 --> 00:01:05.857
She's articulate.

10
00:01:05.940 --> 00:01:07.734
[Carrie speaking]

11
00:01:09.402 --> 00:01:10.236
Smart.

12
00:01:10.320 --> 00:01:12.697
[Carrie speaking]

13
00:01:16.826 --> 00:01:18.244
Yet diabolical.

14
00:01:19.079 --> 00:01:20.538
[man 2 speaking]

15
00:01:24.209 --> 00:01:25.502
[Carrie speaking]

16
00:01:32.092 --> 00:01:33.885
[tense music playing]

17
00:01:39.349 --> 00:01:41.643
[woman 1] So what makes a good neighbor?

18
00:01:43.520 --> 00:01:48.233
[woman 2] I would consider a good neighbor
to be someone who is friendly

19
00:01:48.316 --> 00:01:50.944
but not overbearing.

20
00:01:53.071 --> 00:01:55.907
Not nosy or in your business.

21
00:01:55.990 --> 00:01:59.077
just kind of a friendly wave.

22
00:01:59.869 --> 00:02:05.208
and mostly just leaving me alone. [laughs]

23
00:02:08.837 --> 00:02:12.507
Los Angeles is made up
of many different suburbs.

24
00:02:14.634 --> 00:02:18.221
Some of them are considered nice or safe.

25
00:02:18.930 --> 00:02:21.266
Some of them are considered not so nice.

26
00:02:23.601 --> 00:02:26.980
The Beverly Glen neighborhood
is considered a safe neighborhood.

27
00:02:28.439 --> 00:02:29.607
The neighborhood's gorgeous.

28
00:02:29.691 --> 00:02:32.861
It's kind of borderline in between
Beverly Hills and Century City.

29
00:02:34.487 --> 00:02:38.324
You see a lot of people walking.
walking their kids in strollers.

30
00:02:38.408 --> 00:02:40.034
walking their dogs.

31
00:02:40.994 --> 00:02:44.873
Most of the people who've lived there
lived there for a very long time.

32
00:02:47.083 --> 00:02:51.171
[Bella] The neighborhood is mostly
small apartment buildings.

33
00:02:51.880 --> 00:02:54.883
And there are only six units
in my building.

34
00:02:57.010 --> 00:03:03.016
Caroline Herrling was my neighbor
from the day I moved in to Beverly Glen.

35
00:03:03.099 --> 00:03:05.018
which was around 2016.

36
00:03:05.768 --> 00:03:09.564
From my understanding. she had
been there for a while before I got there.

37
00:03:10.356 --> 00:03:14.819
Carrie's apartment was across from me.
one apartment down.

38
00:03:15.987 --> 00:03:20.825
She had a vibe of being business casual.

39
00:03:21.951 --> 00:03:24.954
She seemed very smiley and cheery

40
00:03:25.038 --> 00:03:27.582
and very normal.

41
00:03:27.665 --> 00:03:30.585
-[dog barking]
-Cha-cha-cha-cha-cha.

42
00:03:30.668 --> 00:03:33.296
[Bella] I would see Carrie
probably twice a week.

43
00:03:33.379 --> 00:03:35.673
walking our dogs at the same time.

44
00:03:36.633 --> 00:03:39.761
And she'd chitchat about the building

45
00:03:39.844 --> 00:03:42.680
or things we had in common about our dogs.

46
00:03:44.224 --> 00:03:47.227
She never really had friends over.

47
00:03:47.310 --> 00:03:50.021
She was kind of a lone wolf.

48
00:03:50.104 --> 00:03:53.650
And I would say the majority
of the people in our building

49
00:03:53.733 --> 00:03:57.737
kept to themselves
and they valued their privacy.

50
00:03:58.321 --> 00:03:59.822
[contemplative music playing]

51
00:04:01.282 --> 00:04:04.827
[Ashley] I moved in in November of 2019.

52
00:04:06.704 --> 00:04:10.166
The building was set up as six townhouses.

53
00:04:10.250 --> 00:04:13.336
and there was three on each side.

54
00:04:13.419 --> 00:04:18.007
I was unit four.
and Carrie's unit was unit six.

55
00:04:18.091 --> 00:04:21.177
So we actually shared a wall.

56
00:04:22.095 --> 00:04:24.013
The first time I met Caroline.

57
00:04:24.097 --> 00:04:26.140
she knocked on my door and I answered.

58
00:04:26.224 --> 00:04:28.393
and she introduced herself as Carrie.

59
00:04:28.476 --> 00:04:30.478
And then she said to me.

60
00:04:30.561 --> 00:04:34.232
"I can come in and check on your dog
when you're not at home."

61
00:04:34.315 --> 00:04:36.317
She just seemed very kind.

62
00:04:36.401 --> 00:04:38.111
like a good neighbor. just very nice.

63
00:04:39.153 --> 00:04:41.447
My husband and I
used to kind of make jokes

64
00:04:41.531 --> 00:04:44.284
that she reminded us
of a kindergarten teacher

65
00:04:44.367 --> 00:04:47.120
because she was just very sweet.

66
00:04:48.621 --> 00:04:51.791
Carrie and I naturally talked about
what we did for a living.

67
00:04:51.874 --> 00:04:54.919
And I told her I did real estate.

68
00:04:55.003 --> 00:04:57.755
And she told me that she was

69
00:04:57.839 --> 00:05:03.094
in charge of handling
trust. wills and probates for people.

70
00:05:04.178 --> 00:05:08.766
And she said that she had a house
in the Valley that was coming up for sale

71
00:05:08.850 --> 00:05:10.768
that was going through probate.

72
00:05:10.852 --> 00:05:13.521
if we were interested in purchasing it.

73
00:05:14.856 --> 00:05:16.733
At the time. my husband and I weren't

74
00:05:16.816 --> 00:05:19.110
looking to purchase
a home or any property.

75
00:05:19.193 --> 00:05:23.197
So we didn't think anything of it
after that conversation.

76
00:05:25.908 --> 00:05:27.535
[tense music playing]

77
00:05:32.415 --> 00:05:35.710
[man] I'm a detective assigned to
the Valley Bureau Homicide Unit.

78
00:05:36.336 --> 00:05:39.339
I've been a detective since 2005.

79
00:05:39.422 --> 00:05:42.467
We get a lot of crazy phone calls
at the station.

80
00:05:42.550 --> 00:05:45.970
We do have an obligation
to investigate them.

81
00:05:46.054 --> 00:05:47.013
[phone ringing]

82
00:05:47.096 --> 00:05:52.352
But an anonymous phone call
that I received back in October of 2021

83
00:05:52.435 --> 00:05:54.520
seemed a little different to me.

84
00:05:54.604 --> 00:05:55.772
I answered the phone

85
00:05:55.855 --> 00:05:59.901
and was met by a female
who seemed kind of nervous to talk to me.

86
00:06:00.985 --> 00:06:02.904
I asked her what was going on.

87
00:06:02.987 --> 00:06:07.283
And she was concerned
for a man named Charles Wilding

88
00:06:07.367 --> 00:06:12.038
and that people had been
using his identity for financial gain.

89
00:06:12.121 --> 00:06:15.124
Working a homicide unit.
I thought instantly.

90
00:06:15.208 --> 00:06:18.544
"Okay. this is a case that
might need to go to financial crimes."

91
00:06:19.545 --> 00:06:24.425
But she did tell me that she thought
that Mr. Wilding was possibly deceased.

92
00:06:24.509 --> 00:06:28.763
And she thought maybe he was dead
as a result of foul play.

93
00:06:28.846 --> 00:06:33.017
Obviously. at this point. this piqued
my interest as a homicide detective.

94
00:06:33.935 --> 00:06:37.105
So I ran the name of Charles Wilding

95
00:06:37.188 --> 00:06:40.733
to see if possibly
he was a victim or a suspect

96
00:06:40.817 --> 00:06:43.277
in any sort of report made to the LAPD.

97
00:06:44.278 --> 00:06:48.950
And I discovered that. in fact.
back in December of 2020.

98
00:06:49.033 --> 00:06:51.327
officers had been
dispatched to Charles' house

99
00:06:51.411 --> 00:06:54.038
because neighbors hadn't
seen him in some days.

100
00:06:54.122 --> 00:06:56.374
They wanted to make sure that he was okay.

101
00:07:06.509 --> 00:07:08.678
[Carrie] Hi. Are you looking for me?

102
00:07:08.761 --> 00:07:10.888
[man 1] No. I'm looking
for Charles Wilding.

103
00:07:10.972 --> 00:07:11.973
[man 2] Do you live here?

104
00:07:12.056 --> 00:07:16.602
[Carrie] I do not live here.
but I'm. um. the trustee of the estate.

105
00:07:16.686 --> 00:07:19.605
-[man 1] Where's he at?
-Charles is… Charles is in Carpinteria.

106
00:07:19.689 --> 00:07:22.942
I talked to the social worker today.
I'm assuming that's why you are here.

107
00:07:23.025 --> 00:07:24.694
-[man 1] Who is it?
-[Carrie] Hang on.

108
00:07:24.777 --> 00:07:26.362
Let me just grab the dog.

109
00:07:26.446 --> 00:07:27.447
[man 1] Okay.

110
00:07:29.907 --> 00:07:31.200
Carpinteria?

111
00:07:31.951 --> 00:07:35.413
Officers had responded to the location

112
00:07:35.496 --> 00:07:37.915
and they had met with a woman.

113
00:07:37.999 --> 00:07:39.959
Caroline Herrling.

114
00:07:40.042 --> 00:07:41.419
[Carrie] It's C-A-R-O.

115
00:07:41.502 --> 00:07:43.671
[man 1] C-A-R-O.

116
00:07:43.754 --> 00:07:44.714
[Carrie] L-I-N-E.

117
00:07:44.797 --> 00:07:45.673
Is it unlocked?

118
00:07:45.756 --> 00:07:47.758
-[woman] It's not. I got the keys.
-[Carrie] Okay.

119
00:07:47.842 --> 00:07:50.219
[Mark] Another woman
came outside of the gate

120
00:07:50.303 --> 00:07:52.680
that Carrie introduced as her assistant.

121
00:07:52.763 --> 00:07:54.015
[Carrie] Yeah. I came on board.

122
00:07:54.098 --> 00:07:56.893
So I'm the successor trustee
for the estate.

123
00:07:56.976 --> 00:08:01.189
Um… And this details that. So…

124
00:08:01.272 --> 00:08:03.733
I've got trust papers in the car
if you wanna see them.

125
00:08:03.816 --> 00:08:05.485
-[man 2] No. it's okay.
-Um…

126
00:08:05.568 --> 00:08:07.320
You said you have a phone number for him?

127
00:08:07.403 --> 00:08:10.490
We wanna make sure he's okay.
somebody's concerned about his welfare.

128
00:08:10.573 --> 00:08:14.327
[Carrie] Yeah. I mean. I can call his
home phone and it goes to his cell phone.

129
00:08:14.410 --> 00:08:16.370
It takes him a couple of days
to call me back.

130
00:08:16.454 --> 00:08:18.539
He doesn't like having
to necessarily talk to me.

131
00:08:18.623 --> 00:08:19.874
He says I talk too much.

132
00:08:19.957 --> 00:08:22.960
Every question the officers
asked these women.

133
00:08:23.044 --> 00:08:24.795
they had an answer for.

134
00:08:24.879 --> 00:08:26.088
[man 2] What's his phone number?

135
00:08:26.172 --> 00:08:27.673
-[Carrie] His number?
-I can transfer…

136
00:08:27.757 --> 00:08:29.383
[Carrie] His phone number is 818…

137
00:08:29.467 --> 00:08:30.843
[Mark] What they were doing there.

138
00:08:30.927 --> 00:08:34.764
what was their relationship
to the Wilding residence.

139
00:08:34.847 --> 00:08:37.225
and where he was staying.

140
00:08:37.308 --> 00:08:38.893
[eerie music playing]

141
00:08:40.478 --> 00:08:41.854
One thing that stood out to me

142
00:08:41.938 --> 00:08:44.857
is when the officers
walked up the hillside to the property.

143
00:08:45.566 --> 00:08:47.985
it was surrounded by a privacy fence.

144
00:08:48.069 --> 00:08:51.948
[man 2] Not that I don't believe you
that he's not here.

145
00:08:52.031 --> 00:08:54.742
but we gotta make sure he's not here.

146
00:08:54.825 --> 00:08:57.370
[Mark] They needed to check the residence
to make sure. in fact.

147
00:08:57.453 --> 00:09:00.206
that Charles wasn't
in any danger inside the home.

148
00:09:00.289 --> 00:09:04.293
Carrie seemed a little hesitant by this.
which again. piqued my curiosity.

149
00:09:04.377 --> 00:09:06.754
-[man 2] Take your word for it.
-Can I get you a mask?

150
00:09:06.837 --> 00:09:09.507
[man 2] This is good enough.
We're not gonna be there long enough.

151
00:09:09.590 --> 00:09:12.301
It's not good enough. trust me.
You don't wanna go in there.

152
00:09:12.385 --> 00:09:13.511
It's really bad.

153
00:09:13.594 --> 00:09:15.429
Like. it's dangerous bad.

154
00:09:15.513 --> 00:09:17.390
[man 2] I think we can deal
with a little mold.

155
00:09:17.473 --> 00:09:18.349
Okay. Okay.

156
00:09:18.432 --> 00:09:20.685
[man 2] We'll take the risk.
We won't hold you liable.

157
00:09:20.768 --> 00:09:21.686
Okay.

158
00:09:22.728 --> 00:09:24.397
Come on. step over things.

159
00:09:25.565 --> 00:09:27.733
So. go this way.

160
00:09:27.817 --> 00:09:29.569
[indistinct chatter on police radio]

161
00:09:36.200 --> 00:09:39.328
You could tell that the house inside
was in complete disarray.

162
00:09:40.288 --> 00:09:42.748
[woman on radio] …count on David 194-645.

163
00:09:42.832 --> 00:09:45.167
[man 2] Is there…
Is there a garage over there?

164
00:09:45.251 --> 00:09:48.170
Yes. there's a garage right there.
Do you wanna go see that?

165
00:09:48.254 --> 00:09:49.213
[man 1] Yeah.

166
00:09:49.297 --> 00:09:50.965
[eerie music continues]

167
00:09:59.015 --> 00:10:01.976
[Carrie] Do you want us to open
that garage door on that side

168
00:10:02.059 --> 00:10:03.519
so you can see in the other way?

169
00:10:03.603 --> 00:10:05.855
-[man 2] Yeah. No?
-[man 1] No. we're good.

170
00:10:05.938 --> 00:10:06.939
[Carrie] You good?

171
00:10:08.733 --> 00:10:12.111
They went through the entire property
and there was no sign of Charles.

172
00:10:12.194 --> 00:10:13.029
Yeah. Yeah.

173
00:10:13.112 --> 00:10:14.614
[man 2] We need to know he's okay.

174
00:10:14.697 --> 00:10:15.615
I understand that.

175
00:10:15.698 --> 00:10:18.034
-Once he's okay. then…
-[man 1] We'll be out of your hair.

176
00:10:18.117 --> 00:10:20.661
Oh. that's okay.
I totally understand that.

177
00:10:20.745 --> 00:10:24.582
I didn't have you sign a release
for the mold. so don't get sick. [laughs]

178
00:10:24.665 --> 00:10:26.042
[man 2] Appreciate the cooperation.

179
00:10:26.125 --> 00:10:28.586
[Carrie] No problem.
I totally understand. guys. Thank you.

180
00:10:29.503 --> 00:10:32.173
After the welfare check conducted by LAPD.

181
00:10:32.256 --> 00:10:36.844
Adult Protective Services was able
to speak with somebody on the phone

182
00:10:36.927 --> 00:10:38.721
claiming to be Charles.

183
00:10:38.804 --> 00:10:40.598
They closed their case in January.

184
00:10:40.681 --> 00:10:42.058
[tense music playing]

185
00:10:49.690 --> 00:10:52.860
[Mark] We are now 10 months removed

186
00:10:52.943 --> 00:10:56.322
from the first time the officers
had interaction with Carrie

187
00:10:56.405 --> 00:10:58.324
at Charles' residence.

188
00:10:58.407 --> 00:11:01.911
Not having ever heard of
this location before. Kingswood Road.

189
00:11:02.787 --> 00:11:08.501
I googled it and found out that
it was in a pretty wealthy suburban area

190
00:11:08.584 --> 00:11:10.836
of Los Angeles. Sherman Oaks.

191
00:11:11.462 --> 00:11:16.175
Sherman Oaks is known to be
home of several celebrities.

192
00:11:16.258 --> 00:11:19.053
The housing prices there are fairly high

193
00:11:19.136 --> 00:11:22.431
in conjunction with
the rest of Los Angeles.

194
00:11:23.808 --> 00:11:27.978
I met with several neighbors
up on the street where Charles lived

195
00:11:28.062 --> 00:11:32.024
and wanted to find out
a little bit about who he was.

196
00:11:32.108 --> 00:11:35.444
And what I learned was.
Charles lived by himself.

197
00:11:36.529 --> 00:11:37.905
He grew up in that house.

198
00:11:37.988 --> 00:11:42.493
and his father
had moved there back in the 1960s.

199
00:11:42.576 --> 00:11:44.495
So that was his childhood home.

200
00:11:45.204 --> 00:11:49.834
His mother. June Wilding.
had died in 2017.

201
00:11:49.917 --> 00:11:51.836
And Charles was an only child.

202
00:11:51.919 --> 00:11:56.382
and he was rarely seen outside the home.

203
00:11:57.049 --> 00:12:00.428
He was described by some neighbors
as maybe peculiar.

204
00:12:00.511 --> 00:12:02.096
definitely reclusive.

205
00:12:02.179 --> 00:12:03.681
but very pleasant.

206
00:12:05.391 --> 00:12:07.935
From my investigation. the Wilding estate.

207
00:12:08.018 --> 00:12:10.521
which included bank accounts.
brokerage accounts.

208
00:12:10.604 --> 00:12:11.772
and retirement accounts.

209
00:12:11.856 --> 00:12:14.066
was worth millions of dollars.

210
00:12:14.942 --> 00:12:17.987
As the trustee.
Carrie had complete autonomy

211
00:12:18.070 --> 00:12:22.783
over these accounts.
including the property itself.

212
00:12:22.867 --> 00:12:25.202
And Carrie also
controls the purse strings.

213
00:12:25.286 --> 00:12:27.246
She would control all the money.

214
00:12:29.582 --> 00:12:32.460
Having the incident report
that the officers made.

215
00:12:32.543 --> 00:12:34.545
I had a contact number for Carrie.

216
00:12:35.963 --> 00:12:38.758
At this point.
I just wanted to find Charles.

217
00:12:38.841 --> 00:12:40.092
So I called her.

218
00:12:40.926 --> 00:12:44.680
and she said
that he was still in Carpinteria.

219
00:12:44.764 --> 00:12:46.515
And I said. "Hey. fantastic."

220
00:12:47.266 --> 00:12:50.186
"Let's get an address for Charles

221
00:12:50.269 --> 00:12:53.773
so I can set eyes on him
and we can close this case."

222
00:12:53.856 --> 00:12:58.194
And I told her that she needed to provide
that information to me within 24 hours.

223
00:12:58.277 --> 00:12:59.945
[music distorts]

224
00:13:00.029 --> 00:13:01.489
[pensive music playing]

225
00:13:04.950 --> 00:13:06.702
[Bella] Carrie was a good neighbor.

226
00:13:07.244 --> 00:13:12.291
but I would say in 2020.
things started to change.

227
00:13:15.377 --> 00:13:18.839
Throughout the months during COVID.
when we were all at home.

228
00:13:18.923 --> 00:13:23.803
we started noticing
differences in Carrie's personality.

229
00:13:24.887 --> 00:13:28.432
[Bella] She started to have
dark circles under her eyes.

230
00:13:28.516 --> 00:13:31.352
She started wearing. you know. hoodies.

231
00:13:32.478 --> 00:13:34.647
She didn't make eye contact.

232
00:13:34.730 --> 00:13:38.526
She wasn't friendly or talkative anymore.

233
00:13:39.819 --> 00:13:41.612
[indistinct chatter]

234
00:13:42.613 --> 00:13:47.952
[Bella] Carrie had some
suspicious characters around.

235
00:13:48.035 --> 00:13:49.787
They would hang out on the stoop.

236
00:13:49.870 --> 00:13:52.665
One of them had an ankle monitor.

237
00:13:53.457 --> 00:13:56.961
It seemed like he had some prison tattoos.

238
00:13:58.045 --> 00:14:01.966
Carrie also got a roommate
around the same time.

239
00:14:02.049 --> 00:14:07.179
She was very thin.
heroin-chic kind of vibe.

240
00:14:07.263 --> 00:14:12.101
and you could tell that
they were up to no good.

241
00:14:12.184 --> 00:14:13.352
[loud banging]

242
00:14:13.936 --> 00:14:19.525
There started to be loud noises
at bizarre times in the night.

243
00:14:19.608 --> 00:14:22.695
and there would be people in and out.

244
00:14:22.778 --> 00:14:25.698
and it sounded like she was up partying.

245
00:14:27.408 --> 00:14:30.286
[Ashley] When Carrie's guests
started coming over.

246
00:14:30.369 --> 00:14:32.997
they had the code.
so they would just type in the code

247
00:14:33.080 --> 00:14:35.457
and come into the building
at all hours of the night.

248
00:14:37.459 --> 00:14:40.838
My husband would try to tell me
not to worry about it.

249
00:14:40.921 --> 00:14:43.799
but I started feeling a little nervous
because of my children.

250
00:14:43.883 --> 00:14:45.885
[loud bass playing through wall]

251
00:14:47.636 --> 00:14:51.557
[Ashley] I would hear Carrie
play loud music most nights.

252
00:14:52.474 --> 00:14:55.519
It would usually start between midnight

253
00:14:55.603 --> 00:14:59.523
and then go all the way on
until about four o'clock in the morning

254
00:14:59.607 --> 00:15:01.734
and sometimes even wake up my children.

255
00:15:03.319 --> 00:15:07.323
One night I was up. it was late at night.
and I was feeding my daughter…

256
00:15:07.406 --> 00:15:08.657
[baby crying]

257
00:15:08.741 --> 00:15:13.203
…and I can hear the voice of two women.
one being Carrie…

258
00:15:15.164 --> 00:15:17.249
and I can hear her say.

259
00:15:17.750 --> 00:15:22.379
"Oh. look. there's more meth over there.
Grab the meth."

260
00:15:24.632 --> 00:15:28.177
And at that moment.
I just felt a sense of shock.

261
00:15:28.260 --> 00:15:29.887
I couldn't believe what I heard.

262
00:15:31.263 --> 00:15:34.975
I now have a neighbor who was using drugs

263
00:15:35.059 --> 00:15:37.645
and was allowing
other people in the building

264
00:15:37.728 --> 00:15:40.064
who were also using drugs with her.

265
00:15:40.981 --> 00:15:44.360
My automatic thought was just fear.

266
00:15:44.985 --> 00:15:47.112
I did not feel safe.

267
00:15:52.201 --> 00:15:56.789
[Bella] I had gone away for the weekend.
and I had ordered some jewelry online.

268
00:15:56.872 --> 00:16:00.250
and it was delivered
while I was out of town.

269
00:16:01.460 --> 00:16:06.131
I came home from my trip. and I was
really excited to open my packages.

270
00:16:06.215 --> 00:16:09.802
and I noticed that
a bunch of them were missing.

271
00:16:11.345 --> 00:16:16.183
I had $3.000 worth of packages
stolen from me.

272
00:16:16.892 --> 00:16:21.230
I confronted the building manager
and everyone in the building.

273
00:16:21.313 --> 00:16:23.107
and I even confronted Carrie.

274
00:16:25.192 --> 00:16:27.778
When I knocked on Carrie's door.

275
00:16:27.861 --> 00:16:31.156
I could tell she was caught off guard.

276
00:16:32.783 --> 00:16:36.912
She seemed like she didn't really want me
to see inside of her apartment.

277
00:16:38.205 --> 00:16:42.418
She just kind of acted like
she didn't know what I was talking about.

278
00:16:42.501 --> 00:16:44.461
"Oh. I'm so sorry that happened."

279
00:16:44.545 --> 00:16:46.005
"That's so weird."

280
00:16:46.088 --> 00:16:48.590
"Oh. did you check with this person?"

281
00:16:48.674 --> 00:16:51.176
And she came off very suspicious.

282
00:16:52.720 --> 00:16:57.516
Management sent out an e-mail to everybody
in the building and basically said

283
00:16:57.599 --> 00:16:59.977
it's a federal crime to take a package.

284
00:17:00.978 --> 00:17:02.646
They would send them all the time.

285
00:17:04.064 --> 00:17:06.900
Then I started thinking in my head.
like. "Oh. my God.

286
00:17:06.984 --> 00:17:09.445
who is this woman
that we're living next to?"

287
00:17:10.320 --> 00:17:13.490
I feel like I don't even know
who she is anymore.

288
00:17:18.495 --> 00:17:20.497
[dramatic music playing]

289
00:17:22.583 --> 00:17:26.670
[Mark] At this point. it was just
a matter of finding the location

290
00:17:26.754 --> 00:17:28.839
where Charles was in Carpinteria

291
00:17:28.922 --> 00:17:31.467
and actually making contact with Charles

292
00:17:31.550 --> 00:17:34.344
so this case could be officially closed.

293
00:17:34.428 --> 00:17:35.429
[phone rings]

294
00:17:35.512 --> 00:17:37.681
The next day. my phone rings.

295
00:17:37.765 --> 00:17:38.891
and it's Carrie.

296
00:17:40.184 --> 00:17:42.311
Said she was in the company of Charles.

297
00:17:42.936 --> 00:17:47.024
I said. "Fantastic.
Let me speak with him."

298
00:17:47.941 --> 00:17:52.905
Elderly voice introduces himself
as Charles. apologizes to me.

299
00:17:53.572 --> 00:17:56.450
tells me that he really
doesn't like a lot of attention

300
00:17:56.533 --> 00:18:01.163
and that he is staying with friends
in the city of Simi Valley.

301
00:18:01.747 --> 00:18:03.916
And provides me an address.

302
00:18:03.999 --> 00:18:07.961
And he also provides me
a new contact phone number for him.

303
00:18:08.670 --> 00:18:12.007
I did ask him a couple of
personal identification questions.

304
00:18:12.091 --> 00:18:15.552
such as. "I needed to verify
your Social Security Number."

305
00:18:15.636 --> 00:18:19.640
His response to me was.
"I don't know it offhand."

306
00:18:20.766 --> 00:18:22.726
which was a little suspicious to me.

307
00:18:22.810 --> 00:18:25.521
Something just doesn't
seem right with this.

308
00:18:26.438 --> 00:18:28.816
But at this point.
I didn't want to let Carrie know

309
00:18:28.899 --> 00:18:30.818
that my suspicions were raised.

310
00:18:30.901 --> 00:18:34.238
so I thanked her
for having Charles call me.

311
00:18:34.321 --> 00:18:38.659
knowing full well
I'm about to take a drive to Simi Valley.

312
00:18:38.742 --> 00:18:40.369
[tense music playing]

313
00:18:43.205 --> 00:18:44.790
I grabbed a partner.

314
00:18:44.873 --> 00:18:50.796
and we took a drive out to the address
provided by quote-unquote "Charles."

315
00:18:50.879 --> 00:18:54.299
and we met with
an individual. um. at that address.

316
00:18:56.135 --> 00:18:57.511
When he answered the door.

317
00:18:57.594 --> 00:19:01.890
I recognized right away it was not Charles
from the photograph I had of him

318
00:19:01.974 --> 00:19:03.767
from his California ID.

319
00:19:04.476 --> 00:19:07.479
And I asked him point-blank.

320
00:19:08.397 --> 00:19:10.107
"Where's Charles Wilding?"

321
00:19:10.732 --> 00:19:13.735
He looked at me.
and he looked at my partner.

322
00:19:13.819 --> 00:19:15.863
and a little nervously said.

323
00:19:15.946 --> 00:19:18.866
"Oh. I remember Charles."

324
00:19:18.949 --> 00:19:22.995
"I knew him years ago. but he's not here."

325
00:19:23.078 --> 00:19:25.330
"He stayed here briefly.

326
00:19:25.414 --> 00:19:29.793
but last I saw.
he had a pocketful of money.

327
00:19:30.377 --> 00:19:32.629
and he just left one day."

328
00:19:32.713 --> 00:19:34.047
[inaudible conversation]

329
00:19:34.131 --> 00:19:36.925
[Mark] So at this point.
I know something's up.

330
00:19:37.509 --> 00:19:39.845
I thanked him for his time.

331
00:19:39.928 --> 00:19:41.597
and returned to the police station

332
00:19:41.680 --> 00:19:43.849
and filed my missing person report.

333
00:19:46.852 --> 00:19:48.395
I start thinking the worst.

334
00:19:49.146 --> 00:19:52.232
It just seems unlikely to me
that a 70-year-old man

335
00:19:52.316 --> 00:19:55.110
can disappear off the face of the Earth.

336
00:19:55.194 --> 00:20:00.782
And those that are supposed to
care for him. take care of him.

337
00:20:00.866 --> 00:20:05.078
are actually lying to me
about everything involving his life.

338
00:20:06.496 --> 00:20:08.957
I needed to zero my focus in on Carrie.

339
00:20:10.542 --> 00:20:13.879
It seems that all roads
are leading back to her.

340
00:20:23.347 --> 00:20:25.140
[woman] Caroline is a chameleon.

341
00:20:25.224 --> 00:20:29.228
but I certainly never thought that
I would be the subject of her wrath.

342
00:20:29.311 --> 00:20:32.773
I never thought she would
turn on me the way she did.

343
00:20:34.983 --> 00:20:38.946
I met Caroline
through a mutual friend in 2003.

344
00:20:40.239 --> 00:20:43.492
I thought Caroline was a smart person.

345
00:20:43.575 --> 00:20:44.660
She's witty.

346
00:20:45.202 --> 00:20:49.289
She held my interest.
We hit it off rather quickly.

347
00:20:51.458 --> 00:20:53.502
Caroline was a social butterfly.

348
00:20:54.461 --> 00:20:57.965
Caroline could talk to men
about cars. sports.

349
00:20:58.048 --> 00:21:01.218
She could talk to women
about fashion. jewelry.

350
00:21:01.718 --> 00:21:03.637
She knew a little bit about everything.

351
00:21:03.720 --> 00:21:06.515
She really was a jack-of-all-trades.

352
00:21:07.391 --> 00:21:10.852
When she first came to LA.
Caroline wanted to be an actress.

353
00:21:11.561 --> 00:21:15.315
She wanted to get out of the Midwest.
That was her ultimate goal.

354
00:21:16.149 --> 00:21:22.489
I felt like she had
big dreams for herself.

355
00:21:23.991 --> 00:21:27.244
but I never knew Caroline
to go on any auditions.

356
00:21:27.327 --> 00:21:28.787
go to a job every day.

357
00:21:28.870 --> 00:21:30.831
I never knew her to get a paycheck.

358
00:21:32.082 --> 00:21:34.501
So when Caroline and I went on trips.

359
00:21:34.584 --> 00:21:36.128
she never paid for anything.

360
00:21:37.045 --> 00:21:39.339
My husband is a film director.

361
00:21:39.423 --> 00:21:42.217
He did pay for our. you know.
first-class travel.

362
00:21:42.301 --> 00:21:45.178
and I took her as my guest

363
00:21:45.262 --> 00:21:49.683
because I felt she was
so good to me in my life.

364
00:21:49.766 --> 00:21:50.934
[thunder cracks]

365
00:21:51.685 --> 00:21:53.854
[Dusty] The last
few years of our friendship.

366
00:21:53.937 --> 00:21:55.897
we were together nearly constantly.

367
00:21:56.648 --> 00:21:58.650
During this time.

368
00:21:58.734 --> 00:22:01.653
Caroline knew that I was
going through my separation.

369
00:22:01.737 --> 00:22:03.530
and I wanted to get a divorce.

370
00:22:04.114 --> 00:22:06.533
So she kind of said.
"Let's do it. We can do this."

371
00:22:06.616 --> 00:22:09.870
"Let's file. I can help you.
You don't need to get a lawyer."

372
00:22:09.953 --> 00:22:11.621
And she took over.

373
00:22:15.042 --> 00:22:19.629
As far as I know.
Caroline never attended law school

374
00:22:19.713 --> 00:22:21.173
or passed any bar.

375
00:22:21.757 --> 00:22:23.842
but she really felt that she knew the law.

376
00:22:23.925 --> 00:22:26.887
So she gave advice.

377
00:22:28.305 --> 00:22:30.015
It was hard. as any divorce would be.

378
00:22:30.098 --> 00:22:32.392
and she was my friend.
I talked to her about it a lot.

379
00:22:32.476 --> 00:22:35.854
And then one day. I got a bill from her

380
00:22:35.937 --> 00:22:38.607
for $152.000.

381
00:22:40.192 --> 00:22:43.487
For the previous two years.
every phone call we had.

382
00:22:43.570 --> 00:22:46.031
she billed me for it like a lawyer would.

383
00:22:47.199 --> 00:22:50.327
I was shocked.
I'm like. "Carrie. what is this?"

384
00:22:50.869 --> 00:22:54.498
She said. "Well. I'm giving you
advice on your divorce.

385
00:22:54.581 --> 00:22:58.293
so my time is not free."

386
00:22:58.377 --> 00:22:59.878
I thought we were friends.

387
00:22:59.961 --> 00:23:03.048
I was just bouncing ideas off of her.

388
00:23:03.757 --> 00:23:06.676
I didn't think we were having
a legal meeting about this.

389
00:23:07.636 --> 00:23:12.349
But she filed a lawsuit against me
for $152.000.

390
00:23:12.849 --> 00:23:16.770
And my ex-husband. too. she sued him
because it was for litigation support.

391
00:23:16.853 --> 00:23:20.774
So she was going after him. basically.
because she knew that he could pay her.

392
00:23:22.734 --> 00:23:25.153
Caroline's lawsuit against
my husband and myself

393
00:23:25.237 --> 00:23:27.406
was a court-order dismissal.

394
00:23:28.448 --> 00:23:30.992
She's not a lawyer.
She can't bill me for legal services.

395
00:23:31.076 --> 00:23:32.869
And the judge tossed it out.

396
00:23:34.371 --> 00:23:38.750
Looking back. I think Caroline
saw dollar signs in her eyes.

397
00:23:38.834 --> 00:23:41.586
I think she targeted me

398
00:23:41.670 --> 00:23:44.714
because she knew
that my ex-husband is a film director.

399
00:23:44.798 --> 00:23:47.926
She thought that he would just
pay her off and not fight the lawsuit.

400
00:23:48.009 --> 00:23:50.137
And she was wrong.

401
00:23:51.054 --> 00:23:52.472
She's a con artist.

402
00:23:52.973 --> 00:23:55.308
[dramatic music playing]

403
00:24:02.399 --> 00:24:05.152
[Mark] At this point. what I know is

404
00:24:05.235 --> 00:24:08.822
officers responded to
Charles' house in December of 2020.

405
00:24:09.322 --> 00:24:10.949
They couldn't get ahold of him.

406
00:24:11.825 --> 00:24:14.578
I contact Carrie 10 months later.

407
00:24:14.661 --> 00:24:16.788
and I tell her
I need to get ahold of Charles.

408
00:24:17.914 --> 00:24:21.710
I speak to an elderly man
that purports to be Charles Wilding

409
00:24:21.793 --> 00:24:24.796
that gives me an address that he's not at.

410
00:24:25.630 --> 00:24:28.675
It should not be hard to find this person.

411
00:24:28.758 --> 00:24:31.303
But in fact. we don't know where he is.

412
00:24:34.014 --> 00:24:38.935
The next day. my partner and I drove
to Carrie's Beverly Glen apartment.

413
00:24:40.770 --> 00:24:42.355
[knocking on door]

414
00:24:43.482 --> 00:24:44.649
[Mark] Good morning.

415
00:24:45.817 --> 00:24:47.569
-[Carrie] Hi. Hi. hi.
-[Mark] Hi.

416
00:24:47.652 --> 00:24:51.072
She invited us in
and told us to have a seat

417
00:24:51.156 --> 00:24:52.657
and asked how she could help us.

418
00:24:52.741 --> 00:24:55.535
[Mark speaking]

419
00:24:59.289 --> 00:25:00.248
[Carrie speaking]

420
00:25:00.332 --> 00:25:02.250
[Mark speaking]

421
00:25:04.753 --> 00:25:07.047
[Carrie speaking]

422
00:25:07.130 --> 00:25:08.215
[Mark speaking]

423
00:25:08.298 --> 00:25:09.174
[Carrie speaking]

424
00:25:09.257 --> 00:25:10.175
[Mark speaking]

425
00:25:10.258 --> 00:25:11.635
-[Carrie] June.
-[Mark] June. Okay.

426
00:25:11.718 --> 00:25:13.428
[Carrie speaking]

427
00:25:15.096 --> 00:25:15.931
[Mark speaking]

428
00:25:16.014 --> 00:25:18.099
[Carrie speaking]

429
00:25:28.360 --> 00:25:29.361
[Mark speaking]

430
00:25:29.861 --> 00:25:34.824
She explained that while
Charles was of sound mind.

431
00:25:34.908 --> 00:25:37.827
he didn't really understand
finance very well.

432
00:25:37.911 --> 00:25:43.792
And so June had asked her
to ensure that Charles was taken care of

433
00:25:43.875 --> 00:25:49.214
with the funds that were left behind
by Charles' father and June Wilding.

434
00:25:49.297 --> 00:25:54.135
And Carrie's sole function
was to ensure Charles' well-being.

435
00:25:55.178 --> 00:25:57.055
[Carrie speaking]

436
00:26:03.979 --> 00:26:04.896
[Mark speaking]

437
00:26:04.980 --> 00:26:06.481
[Carrie speaking]

438
00:26:20.579 --> 00:26:23.290
Carrie seemed a little frazzled.

439
00:26:23.373 --> 00:26:27.419
but she still had answers
to the questions that I had.

440
00:26:27.502 --> 00:26:29.462
[Mark speaking]

441
00:26:30.922 --> 00:26:32.048
[Carrie speaking]

442
00:26:32.132 --> 00:26:33.008
[Mark speaking]

443
00:26:33.091 --> 00:26:34.801
[Carrie speaking]

444
00:26:43.101 --> 00:26:44.019
[Mark speaking]

445
00:26:48.648 --> 00:26:49.691
[Carrie speaking]

446
00:26:49.774 --> 00:26:51.067
[Mark speaking]

447
00:26:51.151 --> 00:26:52.110
[Carrie speaking]

448
00:26:59.451 --> 00:27:01.453
[Mark speaking]

449
00:27:17.719 --> 00:27:19.971
I asked her if she would
call Charles in my presence.

450
00:27:20.055 --> 00:27:23.933
and we could just
put the whole thing to bed right now.

451
00:27:24.476 --> 00:27:26.978
[Carrie speaking]

452
00:27:27.062 --> 00:27:28.188
[Mark speaking]

453
00:27:30.649 --> 00:27:31.524
[Carrie] Yeah.

454
00:27:32.192 --> 00:27:34.653
[Mark] As she went
to go look for her phone.

455
00:27:34.736 --> 00:27:40.241
one thing I did notice was a receipt
from a local cell phone store.

456
00:27:41.159 --> 00:27:44.120
And it was for a cell phone purchase

457
00:27:44.204 --> 00:27:46.623
that was purchased two days prior.

458
00:27:47.332 --> 00:27:50.585
And the phone number
was the same phone number

459
00:27:50.669 --> 00:27:54.422
that was provided to me
by the Charles Wilding

460
00:27:54.506 --> 00:27:56.341
I had spoke to on the phone.

461
00:27:56.424 --> 00:27:58.176
And I thought it a little suspicious

462
00:27:58.259 --> 00:28:01.346
that a receipt for
that exact same phone number

463
00:28:01.429 --> 00:28:03.181
was on Carrie's coffee table.

464
00:28:05.225 --> 00:28:06.559
She called the number.

465
00:28:07.394 --> 00:28:09.104
[Carrie speaking]

466
00:28:18.113 --> 00:28:20.865
[Mark speaking]

467
00:28:20.949 --> 00:28:22.158
[Carrie speaking]

468
00:28:25.161 --> 00:28:27.247
[Mark speaking]

469
00:28:27.330 --> 00:28:28.540
[Carrie speaking]

470
00:28:28.623 --> 00:28:29.791
[Mark speaking]

471
00:28:35.755 --> 00:28:37.966
[Carrie speaking]

472
00:28:40.885 --> 00:28:43.722
[Mark] I remember leaving the apartment
with my partner.

473
00:28:44.597 --> 00:28:47.308
and I looked at him and I said.

474
00:28:47.392 --> 00:28:49.352
"I don't like where this is going."

475
00:28:49.436 --> 00:28:50.979
[intense music playing]

476
00:28:52.397 --> 00:28:57.026
So I dig a little deeper into the trust
documents for the Wilding estate.

477
00:28:57.861 --> 00:29:02.365
I located a notary
on one of the trust documents.

478
00:29:03.408 --> 00:29:05.785
And I wanted to find out if. in fact.

479
00:29:05.869 --> 00:29:09.456
Charles Wilding's signature
was in the notary journals

480
00:29:09.539 --> 00:29:13.126
as it was on the document for the trust.

481
00:29:13.209 --> 00:29:14.419
And it was not.

482
00:29:15.086 --> 00:29:17.881
However. in looking through
the notary journals.

483
00:29:17.964 --> 00:29:23.928
I did find out that the day that Charles
allegedly had his signature notarized.

484
00:29:24.012 --> 00:29:27.474
Carrie Herrling was a client
of the notary public.

485
00:29:28.349 --> 00:29:29.601
So at this point.

486
00:29:29.684 --> 00:29:34.606
I am quite certain that
at least this document is a forgery.

487
00:29:34.689 --> 00:29:39.527
And likely the entire trust was a forgery.

488
00:29:42.071 --> 00:29:44.157
As a homicide investigator.

489
00:29:44.240 --> 00:29:48.953
I'm not in tune very much
with white-collar crime.

490
00:29:49.037 --> 00:29:50.580
And I knew I needed some help.

491
00:29:54.876 --> 00:29:56.878
[tense music playing]

492
00:29:58.922 --> 00:30:02.050
[Bella] At this point.
the other neighbors and I.

493
00:30:02.133 --> 00:30:04.761
we were all pretty infuriated

494
00:30:04.844 --> 00:30:07.180
because our safety was at risk.

495
00:30:08.681 --> 00:30:12.519
[Ashley] I told my husband. "I'm going
to write a letter to management."

496
00:30:13.269 --> 00:30:15.647
I wanted them to actually know.

497
00:30:15.730 --> 00:30:19.234
"Hey. my neighbor. I feel like. is crazy.

498
00:30:19.317 --> 00:30:22.153
and I feel unsafe."

499
00:30:24.113 --> 00:30:29.244
But we learned from our building manager
that Carrie was getting evicted.

500
00:30:30.829 --> 00:30:37.085
On top of many other residents complaining
about Carrie and her friends.

501
00:30:37.877 --> 00:30:40.171
she also wasn't paying rent.

502
00:30:40.255 --> 00:30:43.633
So me and all the neighbors were thrilled.

503
00:30:43.716 --> 00:30:49.639
We all had this bonding experience
over this shared traumatic experience.

504
00:30:50.849 --> 00:30:54.811
We were all just relieved
to have her gone.

505
00:30:56.312 --> 00:30:57.897
[upbeat music playing]

506
00:30:59.732 --> 00:31:02.235
[woman] West Hills is
a very residential area.

507
00:31:02.318 --> 00:31:04.028
mostly family oriented.

508
00:31:05.071 --> 00:31:07.448
I've lived in West Hills.
in the same house.

509
00:31:07.532 --> 00:31:09.701
for about 25 years now.

510
00:31:10.326 --> 00:31:11.911
It was a great place to raise my kids.

511
00:31:14.289 --> 00:31:19.043
Caroline moved next door to me
on Easter Sunday of 2022.

512
00:31:20.628 --> 00:31:22.463
Before Caroline moved in.

513
00:31:22.547 --> 00:31:25.717
the house next door was owned by a man

514
00:31:25.800 --> 00:31:28.511
who lived there for at least 35 years

515
00:31:28.595 --> 00:31:30.054
and was a great neighbor.

516
00:31:31.848 --> 00:31:34.559
The first time I met Caroline Herrling.

517
00:31:34.642 --> 00:31:37.854
I was out walking my dogs
on Easter Sunday.

518
00:31:38.855 --> 00:31:41.024
and she was out in the front yard.

519
00:31:41.941 --> 00:31:45.486
So I stopped to introduce myself
and welcome her to the neighborhood.

520
00:31:47.655 --> 00:31:50.950
Caroline told me
she was a litigation consultant.

521
00:31:51.034 --> 00:31:54.203
and she told me that
she was burnt out on practicing law

522
00:31:54.287 --> 00:31:56.706
and she wanted to open
a sober living home.

523
00:31:56.789 --> 00:31:57.957
[ominous music playing]

524
00:31:58.041 --> 00:32:01.252
As soon as she said that.
my heart dropped into my stomach

525
00:32:01.336 --> 00:32:02.754
and I felt nauseous.

526
00:32:03.588 --> 00:32:07.675
I was very concerned about
what might be going on next door

527
00:32:07.759 --> 00:32:10.261
and what changes
that might bring to the neighborhood.

528
00:32:12.263 --> 00:32:14.098
But giving her the benefit of the doubt.

529
00:32:14.182 --> 00:32:18.019
I thought maybe she was doing this
to pay it forward and help others.

530
00:32:24.484 --> 00:32:26.152
[tense music playing]

531
00:32:31.616 --> 00:32:34.619
[Lyndon] When Detective O'Donnell
came to me.

532
00:32:34.702 --> 00:32:37.413
he thought the federal resources
that I could bring

533
00:32:37.497 --> 00:32:39.707
might help him unravel
what happened to Charles.

534
00:32:41.000 --> 00:32:43.628
I've been a postal inspector for 20 years.

535
00:32:43.711 --> 00:32:48.007
I specialize in
investigating financial crimes.

536
00:32:48.091 --> 00:32:51.427
and it seemed to be a fraud investigation

537
00:32:51.511 --> 00:32:53.680
wrapped up in a potential homicide.

538
00:32:55.348 --> 00:32:57.642
The first thing I do in an investigation

539
00:32:57.725 --> 00:32:59.477
is pull bank records.

540
00:32:59.560 --> 00:33:00.979
It's a long process.

541
00:33:01.062 --> 00:33:06.275
but once I have the records.
I look for large transactions.

542
00:33:06.359 --> 00:33:09.946
I can see money moving
from Charles' accounts

543
00:33:10.029 --> 00:33:12.281
into a Caroline Herrling bank account.

544
00:33:12.365 --> 00:33:15.284
and I noticed she was spending the money.

545
00:33:15.368 --> 00:33:19.330
A true trustee does not
spend the money for themselves.

546
00:33:19.414 --> 00:33:21.082
[dramatic music playing]

547
00:33:23.876 --> 00:33:26.921
[Mark] After I enlisted
the help of Inspector Versoza.

548
00:33:27.005 --> 00:33:31.592
I discovered that Carrie had been evicted
from the Beverly Glen property.

549
00:33:31.676 --> 00:33:35.763
and this West Hills house
was being run by Carrie

550
00:33:35.847 --> 00:33:37.724
as a sober-living facility.

551
00:33:38.516 --> 00:33:40.768
Basically. a court-ordered rehab facility.

552
00:33:43.187 --> 00:33:45.440
Whoever runs the sober-living facility

553
00:33:45.523 --> 00:33:50.028
is paid by either the city
or the state or the county

554
00:33:50.111 --> 00:33:51.904
to run that program.

555
00:33:53.531 --> 00:33:56.034
So my suspicions were
this could be another scam.

556
00:33:58.077 --> 00:34:02.331
About a month after Caroline moved in.
that's when the problems started.

557
00:34:04.083 --> 00:34:07.253
As the sober-living residents moved in.

558
00:34:07.336 --> 00:34:10.631
there were lots of people
coming in and out of the house.

559
00:34:10.715 --> 00:34:12.717
-[deep bass music playing]
-[party chatter]

560
00:34:12.800 --> 00:34:17.680
[Lisa] But along with the people
came a yard full of trash. broken windows.

561
00:34:18.306 --> 00:34:20.433
It started looking like a junkyard.

562
00:34:21.517 --> 00:34:24.270
And there was a lot of very loud music.

563
00:34:25.480 --> 00:34:29.400
Start as early as 8:00 in the morning
and go till 2:00 in the morning.

564
00:34:30.318 --> 00:34:34.113
as well as marijuana
smelling till all hours of the night.

565
00:34:35.531 --> 00:34:37.909
Just didn't seem there was any evidence

566
00:34:37.992 --> 00:34:41.204
of any attempt at sober-living
and rehab going on here.

567
00:34:42.830 --> 00:34:44.207
As time went on.

568
00:34:44.290 --> 00:34:48.002
the concern for my kids' safety
just kept escalating.

569
00:34:48.961 --> 00:34:51.631
While I was out walking
my dogs one morning.

570
00:34:51.714 --> 00:34:55.009
there was a man sitting in his car
with the door open.

571
00:34:55.093 --> 00:34:57.470
but he was slumped
over the steering wheel.

572
00:34:58.054 --> 00:35:01.307
It appeared as if he was
likely passed out on drugs.

573
00:35:02.809 --> 00:35:05.520
I did try to call 911
and spoke to another neighbor

574
00:35:05.603 --> 00:35:08.731
who said he'd already seen it
and called it in.

575
00:35:09.315 --> 00:35:11.317
Many of the neighbors were concerned.

576
00:35:12.151 --> 00:35:14.362
So with all the incidents
that were building up.

577
00:35:14.445 --> 00:35:16.948
we started to get together
as a neighborhood watch

578
00:35:17.031 --> 00:35:20.451
to make sure that we were
recording all the things going on.

579
00:35:20.535 --> 00:35:24.288
It was starting to feel terrifying
living next door to Caroline.

580
00:35:32.797 --> 00:35:35.883
[man] I'm an assistant
United States attorney.

581
00:35:35.967 --> 00:35:40.680
Currently. I'm the identity theft
coordinator in Los Angeles.

582
00:35:41.514 --> 00:35:45.768
Something bad had happened to Mr. Wilding.

583
00:35:45.852 --> 00:35:49.063
but we didn't know what it was.

584
00:35:50.857 --> 00:35:54.861
[Lyndon] We knew Caroline Herrling
falsified documents to the court

585
00:35:54.944 --> 00:35:57.655
saying she's a trustee
of June Wilding's estate.

586
00:35:58.239 --> 00:36:00.324
We knew the bank accounts that she looted.

587
00:36:00.408 --> 00:36:05.329
and we found that
she used money from Charles' estate

588
00:36:05.413 --> 00:36:07.874
to buy a home in West Hills.

589
00:36:08.791 --> 00:36:10.960
When we felt our investigation was ready.

590
00:36:11.043 --> 00:36:14.380
our next step was
to execute a search warrant.

591
00:36:15.506 --> 00:36:17.300
[Andrew] The court granted us

592
00:36:17.383 --> 00:36:21.387
a search warrant
for her current residence.

593
00:36:21.470 --> 00:36:23.055
[tense music playing]

594
00:36:25.683 --> 00:36:29.520
[Lisa] On the morning of the raid.
the street was filled with cop cars.

595
00:36:29.604 --> 00:36:30.479
[sirens blaring]

596
00:36:30.563 --> 00:36:34.025
[Lisa] It was. "Come out with
your hands up. You are surrounded."

597
00:36:34.734 --> 00:36:38.029
So I told the kids. "Don't go to school."

598
00:36:38.112 --> 00:36:40.114
"You're not walking out
in the middle of this."

599
00:36:40.198 --> 00:36:43.159
"I don't know what's going on.
Just stay inside."

600
00:36:43.743 --> 00:36:47.246
"Oh my gosh. there's something big
going on at the sober house."

601
00:36:49.373 --> 00:36:52.835
[Lyndon] I was present.
along with probably 20 detectives.

602
00:36:52.919 --> 00:36:56.923
and the detectives and officers
surrounded the house.

603
00:36:57.632 --> 00:36:59.133
and it was full of people.

604
00:36:59.759 --> 00:37:02.678
Caroline had just been
woken up by us at 6:00 a.m..

605
00:37:02.762 --> 00:37:04.430
trying to hide her nervousness.

606
00:37:04.513 --> 00:37:05.723
but it was obvious.

607
00:37:06.307 --> 00:37:09.393
What we found at the house
was absolutely shocking.

608
00:37:10.686 --> 00:37:13.814
It almost seemed
like something out of a movie scene.

609
00:37:15.274 --> 00:37:18.402
She had 16 firearms.

610
00:37:18.486 --> 00:37:24.867
including assault rifles
zip-tied to her bedroom closet door.

611
00:37:24.951 --> 00:37:26.577
many of them loaded.

612
00:37:27.203 --> 00:37:30.581
And several of them
being untraceable ghost guns.

613
00:37:31.249 --> 00:37:32.875
[Lyndon] We found heroin. methamphetamine.

614
00:37:32.959 --> 00:37:34.835
They had scales. the baggies.

615
00:37:34.919 --> 00:37:37.380
They had all the indications
of drug dealing.

616
00:37:38.381 --> 00:37:41.425
In one of the drawers were police badges.

617
00:37:42.009 --> 00:37:44.178
federal badges. DEA.

618
00:37:44.262 --> 00:37:46.597
FBI ID cards.

619
00:37:46.681 --> 00:37:47.807
That was unusual.

620
00:37:47.890 --> 00:37:49.225
[dramatic music playing]

621
00:37:49.308 --> 00:37:53.479
[Mark] We discovered multiple items
connected to the Wilding estate.

622
00:37:53.562 --> 00:37:56.148
Bank statements. account statements.

623
00:37:56.232 --> 00:37:59.151
account holdings from June Wilding.

624
00:37:59.235 --> 00:38:01.862
From an investigative standpoint.

625
00:38:01.946 --> 00:38:03.030
that was a jackpot.

626
00:38:04.740 --> 00:38:09.662
The evidence we seized confirmed
what we thought now to be true.

627
00:38:09.745 --> 00:38:14.041
that Caroline had stolen all his money
and used fraudulent documents.

628
00:38:14.125 --> 00:38:17.670
We also found evidence
that showed this was bigger

629
00:38:17.753 --> 00:38:18.963
than just Charles Wilding.

630
00:38:19.755 --> 00:38:23.509
She was involved
in defrauding other estates.

631
00:38:23.592 --> 00:38:27.388
I knew I had her for bank fraud.
wire fraud. for identity theft.

632
00:38:27.972 --> 00:38:29.807
But the real question I had:

633
00:38:31.017 --> 00:38:32.643
what happened to Charles?

634
00:38:33.477 --> 00:38:35.396
[Mark] We placed Carrie under arrest

635
00:38:35.479 --> 00:38:38.899
and we decided to
Interview her at the property.

636
00:38:41.027 --> 00:38:42.820
[Lyndon speaking]

637
00:38:46.574 --> 00:38:48.200
[Carrie speaking]

638
00:38:57.043 --> 00:38:59.128
[Mark speaking]

639
00:39:05.259 --> 00:39:07.386
[Carrie speaking]

640
00:39:11.849 --> 00:39:12.808
[Mark speaking]

641
00:39:14.643 --> 00:39:15.895
I knew she was lying.

642
00:39:17.313 --> 00:39:21.400
By this time.
Charles had not been seen in two years.

643
00:39:21.901 --> 00:39:24.487
At that point.
we suspected that he was dead.

644
00:39:26.155 --> 00:39:27.323
[Lyndon] So. Carrie.

645
00:39:29.575 --> 00:39:31.911
People were defrauded. you profited.

646
00:39:32.453 --> 00:39:33.829
You're in serious trouble.

647
00:39:33.913 --> 00:39:36.499
-[Mark] It's a house of cards.
-[Lyndon] House of cards. All lies.

648
00:39:37.166 --> 00:39:39.835
[Mark] And it starts with
the Wilding trust that does not exist.

649
00:39:39.919 --> 00:39:42.755
[Carrie] But the trust isn't fake.

650
00:39:43.631 --> 00:39:44.757
[Mark] It's a forgery.

651
00:39:44.840 --> 00:39:45.966
No.

652
00:39:46.050 --> 00:39:47.968
-[Mark] Carrie.
-How is that possible?

653
00:39:48.052 --> 00:39:50.179
[Mark] Well. you have no idea
who the Wildings are.

654
00:39:50.262 --> 00:39:51.514
I do.

655
00:39:51.597 --> 00:39:53.933
Like. I didn't forge these things.

656
00:39:54.016 --> 00:39:56.227
[Lyndon] Let's change gears.
You didn't forge anything.

657
00:39:56.310 --> 00:40:02.024
All we really want is to find
where the body of Charles is.

658
00:40:02.108 --> 00:40:05.069
Did you find his body
deceased in his house?

659
00:40:05.152 --> 00:40:07.446
Or did you have something
to do with his death?

660
00:40:07.530 --> 00:40:09.657
No. I haven't had anything
to do with his death.

661
00:40:09.740 --> 00:40:11.117
I didn't even know he was dead.

662
00:40:11.200 --> 00:40:13.869
It's time to stop. You do not know him.

663
00:40:13.953 --> 00:40:19.500
This is an elaborate fraud scheme
that stops today.

664
00:40:20.334 --> 00:40:22.253
I have told you guys what I know.

665
00:40:22.336 --> 00:40:24.255
As you can see. I try to help people.

666
00:40:24.338 --> 00:40:28.175
I was just literally just trying
to help Charles in all of this.

667
00:40:29.844 --> 00:40:32.179
[Mark] I didn't think
she was truthful at all.

668
00:40:32.721 --> 00:40:35.641
We knew that
something terrible happened to Charles.

669
00:40:38.144 --> 00:40:40.813
[Lyndon] Between all the stocks
and bank accounts.

670
00:40:40.896 --> 00:40:45.568
Charles Wilding's estate was
probably worth about a million dollars.

671
00:40:45.651 --> 00:40:49.822
plus the home. which was worth
between $2 to $2.5 million.

672
00:40:50.656 --> 00:40:55.244
Caroline Herrling established
several trust accounts

673
00:40:55.327 --> 00:40:57.329
in the name of the June Wilding Trust.

674
00:40:58.581 --> 00:41:02.293
And between November 2020 and March 2022.

675
00:41:02.376 --> 00:41:06.505
in one account.
she transacted almost $600.000

676
00:41:06.589 --> 00:41:10.718
from the June Wilding account
to a fake trust account

677
00:41:10.801 --> 00:41:12.803
that she created in her own name.

678
00:41:15.055 --> 00:41:18.350
[Mark] One of the accounts
had a co-account holder

679
00:41:18.976 --> 00:41:21.228
by the name of Jason Kroth.

680
00:41:21.312 --> 00:41:22.897
[tense music playing]

681
00:41:22.980 --> 00:41:25.900
Jason Kroth is a career criminal.

682
00:41:26.484 --> 00:41:27.776
He's an ex-con.

683
00:41:27.860 --> 00:41:30.905
He's a drug user. drug dealer. thief.

684
00:41:30.988 --> 00:41:32.406
He's a fraudster.

685
00:41:32.948 --> 00:41:37.578
I want to know why he is on
bank accounts with Carrie Herrling.

686
00:41:38.329 --> 00:41:42.750
And I want to know everything
that he knows about Charles Wilding.

687
00:41:45.711 --> 00:41:47.588
We found him at a motel.

688
00:41:47.671 --> 00:41:50.341
He was arrested in the parking lot.

689
00:41:51.759 --> 00:41:54.178
We interviewed Jason that evening.

690
00:41:54.261 --> 00:41:55.804
I'm gonna read you your rights. Okay?

691
00:41:55.888 --> 00:41:57.932
[Lyndon] Jason knew Caroline Herrling

692
00:41:58.015 --> 00:42:00.684
because they're both
methamphetamine users.

693
00:42:00.768 --> 00:42:04.230
And eventually.
as they continued the scheme.

694
00:42:04.313 --> 00:42:06.482
fell into a romantic relationship.

695
00:42:07.900 --> 00:42:10.569
[Mark] This is a real test
of your honesty.

696
00:42:10.653 --> 00:42:12.446
-[Jason] Okay.
-[Mark] Okay. Jason? Because…

697
00:42:12.530 --> 00:42:13.447
[Jason] All right.

698
00:42:13.531 --> 00:42:17.618
[Mark] We can account for his money.
and we can account for his property.

699
00:42:17.701 --> 00:42:22.456
but Charles just up and vanishes
like a fucking fart in church.

700
00:42:23.082 --> 00:42:27.878
And not one fucking person
can look us in the eye

701
00:42:27.962 --> 00:42:32.675
and say. "You know what?
If you go here or you go there.

702
00:42:34.134 --> 00:42:35.594
you may find something."

703
00:42:35.678 --> 00:42:37.972
[dramatic music playing]

704
00:42:38.055 --> 00:42:41.058
[Mark] Let's talk about
Kingswood Drive and the Wildings.

705
00:42:42.977 --> 00:42:48.107
He admits to looking
for properties in affluent areas

706
00:42:48.190 --> 00:42:50.568
that he can potentially burglarize.

707
00:42:51.902 --> 00:42:54.446
He had found the Wilding property.

708
00:42:54.530 --> 00:42:57.324
and he had. in fact.
broken into that property.

709
00:42:59.660 --> 00:43:01.036
[Jason] I… I went in the house.

710
00:43:01.120 --> 00:43:02.204
[door creaking]

711
00:43:02.288 --> 00:43:04.582
[Jason] And I took
some jewelry that was there.

712
00:43:04.665 --> 00:43:06.458
-[Mark] Okay.
-[Jason] Um. that's when…

713
00:43:07.876 --> 00:43:09.003
I smelled a smell.

714
00:43:10.921 --> 00:43:12.214
It was bad. It was…

715
00:43:15.259 --> 00:43:21.223
And then I kinda shined the light up
and I see old what's-his-face.

716
00:43:22.600 --> 00:43:24.602
-His mouth was open a little bit.
-[rodent squeaking]

717
00:43:24.685 --> 00:43:27.396
And it was just crazy.

718
00:43:27.479 --> 00:43:30.733
-There was. like. rats and shit.
-[rats squeaking]

719
00:43:30.816 --> 00:43:33.444
-I mean. they were in his mouth.
-[Mark chuckles] Okay.

720
00:43:33.527 --> 00:43:35.779
[Jason] Yeah. he was far. far gone.

721
00:43:37.364 --> 00:43:39.950
Yeah. he was… He was dead.

722
00:43:40.034 --> 00:43:41.619
[squeaking continues]

723
00:43:42.369 --> 00:43:43.871
[Jason] He was definitely dead.

724
00:43:46.040 --> 00:43:48.125
So I asked him. what did he do?

725
00:43:48.208 --> 00:43:50.044
And his response to me was.

726
00:43:50.127 --> 00:43:51.629
"Well. I called Carrie."

727
00:43:53.714 --> 00:43:57.468
[Lyndon] When Jason found
financial documents in Charles' house.

728
00:43:57.551 --> 00:43:59.928
he knew he needed to go to somebody

729
00:44:00.012 --> 00:44:04.475
who'd be able to handle
this type of fraud scheme.

730
00:44:05.434 --> 00:44:07.770
[Lyndon] How much money
did you make out of Charles?

731
00:44:08.520 --> 00:44:11.231
Like 140 or something.

732
00:44:11.315 --> 00:44:13.442
[Lyndon] $140.000? Okay.

733
00:44:13.525 --> 00:44:14.777
Who was paying you?

734
00:44:14.860 --> 00:44:15.986
[Jason] Uh. Caroline.

735
00:44:17.571 --> 00:44:19.031
[Lyndon] So who got rid of the body?

736
00:44:20.866 --> 00:44:21.742
[Jason mumbles]

737
00:44:21.825 --> 00:44:23.202
-[Lydon] Who did?
-Caroline.

738
00:44:23.285 --> 00:44:24.370
[Lyndon] With whom?

739
00:44:24.995 --> 00:44:26.205
[mumbling]

740
00:44:26.872 --> 00:44:28.248
-[Lyndon] With you?
-No.

741
00:44:28.332 --> 00:44:29.249
[Lyndon] With whom?

742
00:44:33.295 --> 00:44:36.048
-[Mark] This is the honest part.
-She brought her with her.

743
00:44:36.632 --> 00:44:38.676
[Lyndon] Her and… carried
the body by themselves.

744
00:44:38.759 --> 00:44:39.843
Definitely.

745
00:44:40.719 --> 00:44:42.721
[Lyndon] This shit's gonna haunt you.

746
00:44:42.805 --> 00:44:44.431
No. I'm telling you what happened.

747
00:44:44.932 --> 00:44:47.267
[Lyndon] The soul of this body
is going to haunt you.

748
00:44:47.351 --> 00:44:48.644
She took it to her house.

749
00:44:50.104 --> 00:44:51.438
[Lyndon] Beverly Glen?

750
00:44:52.981 --> 00:44:54.358
How did she carry it there?

751
00:44:54.983 --> 00:44:55.901
[Jason] Her Jeep.

752
00:44:55.984 --> 00:44:57.861
After they put it in bags. You know?

753
00:44:57.945 --> 00:44:59.238
[Mark] They put it in bags?

754
00:44:59.321 --> 00:45:00.989
Big bag. Big bags. yes.

755
00:45:01.824 --> 00:45:04.493
They described to me when they
picked him up. when they picked…

756
00:45:04.576 --> 00:45:05.828
He'd been there for a minute.

757
00:45:05.911 --> 00:45:08.205
I mean. a minute.
Like. he was stuck into the floor.

758
00:45:08.288 --> 00:45:12.000
[Mark] Jason's pointing a finger
at Carrie and her assistant.

759
00:45:12.710 --> 00:45:13.627
I'm thinking.

760
00:45:13.711 --> 00:45:16.839
is this something that
perhaps he did himself

761
00:45:16.922 --> 00:45:19.174
and he's trying to put
the blame on somebody else?

762
00:45:19.967 --> 00:45:22.928
But Carrie surprises me at every turn.

763
00:45:23.470 --> 00:45:25.597
Who knew what she could be capable of?

764
00:45:28.809 --> 00:45:30.477
[dramatic music intensifies]

765
00:45:32.521 --> 00:45:36.191
After interviewing Jason Kroth.
we wanted to dig a little further.

766
00:45:37.735 --> 00:45:40.612
So we went back to the Wilding residence.

767
00:45:43.323 --> 00:45:45.075
According to Jason Kroth.

768
00:45:45.159 --> 00:45:47.286
when Carrie was cleaning out the house.

769
00:45:47.369 --> 00:45:49.288
after Charles was removed.

770
00:45:49.371 --> 00:45:52.249
she went so far
as to remove the floorboards

771
00:45:52.332 --> 00:45:54.710
to get rid of any potential evidence

772
00:45:54.793 --> 00:45:56.670
that somebody had died in that home.

773
00:46:00.174 --> 00:46:02.426
At this point.
the house was completely empty.

774
00:46:03.427 --> 00:46:05.929
But in the second-floor bedroom.

775
00:46:06.013 --> 00:46:08.223
we noticed plywood on the floor.

776
00:46:10.768 --> 00:46:12.269
But once we lifted the plywood.

777
00:46:13.270 --> 00:46:16.023
the floor was gone.
but the subfloor was there.

778
00:46:16.106 --> 00:46:19.943
And we saw there was a stain on the floor

779
00:46:20.611 --> 00:46:23.322
in the shape of what could be a human.

780
00:46:25.824 --> 00:46:28.327
So at this point. we knew

781
00:46:28.410 --> 00:46:30.746
there's some truth to what Jason said.

782
00:46:32.456 --> 00:46:35.125
So we decided to confront Caroline.

783
00:46:35.626 --> 00:46:38.128
and we set her up with a polygraph.

784
00:46:38.212 --> 00:46:40.297
[man] Come on in here. Are you Caroline?

785
00:46:40.380 --> 00:46:41.298
I am.

786
00:46:43.634 --> 00:46:46.053
[man] I don't care what
you've told the investigators

787
00:46:46.136 --> 00:46:48.138
up to this point in time.

788
00:46:48.222 --> 00:46:51.850
If there's more to this situation

789
00:46:51.934 --> 00:46:55.437
than you told investigators before.

790
00:46:55.521 --> 00:46:59.983
do not minimize your involvement.

791
00:47:00.651 --> 00:47:02.653
and do not lie or leave anything out.

792
00:47:03.737 --> 00:47:05.656
[Lyndon] Caroline Herrling
was initially charged

793
00:47:05.739 --> 00:47:09.785
with a conspiracy to commit
wire fraud and identity theft.

794
00:47:09.868 --> 00:47:13.455
and she was charged with
distributing controlled substances.

795
00:47:13.539 --> 00:47:17.042
She was facing a huge sentence.

796
00:47:17.918 --> 00:47:19.169
[man] The Wilding property.

797
00:47:19.253 --> 00:47:21.046
How did you first learn about it?

798
00:47:21.588 --> 00:47:24.925
Through a guy named Jason Kroth.
Who is also…

799
00:47:25.008 --> 00:47:26.969
-[man] Jason Kroth. Okay.
-Yup.

800
00:47:27.594 --> 00:47:30.681
Jason took us to the house where…

801
00:47:32.140 --> 00:47:34.226
where Charles Wilding
was already deceased.

802
00:47:34.309 --> 00:47:35.394
[man] Okay.

803
00:47:36.478 --> 00:47:40.023
Finally. she admitted
Charles was indeed dead.

804
00:47:40.107 --> 00:47:43.151
and to me. that was groundbreaking.

805
00:47:43.902 --> 00:47:45.988
Caroline wanted a lighter sentence.

806
00:47:46.071 --> 00:47:50.325
and part of that lighter sentence required
her to be truthful about what she did.

807
00:47:50.826 --> 00:47:54.788
Ultimately. she knew
when we put her in a polygraph.

808
00:47:54.872 --> 00:47:56.540
we would catch her in a lie.

809
00:47:56.623 --> 00:47:58.458
[Carrie] Because he was already deceased.

810
00:47:58.542 --> 00:48:01.962
it would be a victimless crime
because he didn't have any family.

811
00:48:02.504 --> 00:48:03.881
[man] You wanted to keep Charles…

812
00:48:03.964 --> 00:48:06.300
-Alive.
-[man] Okay. I got you.

813
00:48:06.383 --> 00:48:09.094
Technically. because there was
some access they couldn't get

814
00:48:09.177 --> 00:48:10.387
to certain bank accounts.

815
00:48:12.097 --> 00:48:18.520
If anyone had discovered
that Charles Wilding was really dead.

816
00:48:18.604 --> 00:48:25.485
Caroline Herrling would not have been able
to access his assets ever again.

817
00:48:25.569 --> 00:48:30.032
and that's why she went
to such extraordinary efforts

818
00:48:30.115 --> 00:48:35.370
to make it seem
that Charles Wilding was still alive.

819
00:48:35.454 --> 00:48:38.916
[man] What's your understanding
of what happened with Charles' body?

820
00:48:38.999 --> 00:48:40.375
I have no idea.

821
00:48:40.459 --> 00:48:44.463
I gave the officers every place
I think that it could have gone.

822
00:48:46.590 --> 00:48:48.759
but I honestly don't know where it is.

823
00:48:49.593 --> 00:48:51.803
[man] Well. it's alleged
that Charles' body

824
00:48:51.887 --> 00:48:56.183
ended up back
at your residence at Beverly Glen.

825
00:48:57.643 --> 00:49:00.771
The only way you get through this exam
successfully today

826
00:49:01.647 --> 00:49:07.027
is being 100% honest and candid
in regards to your involvement

827
00:49:07.110 --> 00:49:12.199
with the disposal
of Charles Wilding's remains.

828
00:49:17.162 --> 00:49:19.081
So let me just ask it this way.

829
00:49:19.790 --> 00:49:22.542
Is there more that
you want to share with me

830
00:49:22.626 --> 00:49:26.338
about your involvement
and the disposal of his body

831
00:49:26.421 --> 00:49:28.256
-before we go further?
-Yes.

832
00:49:28.340 --> 00:49:29.299
-Yeah.
-[man] Okay.

833
00:49:30.133 --> 00:49:32.678
At this point. she broke.

834
00:49:33.178 --> 00:49:34.846
[dramatic music playing]

835
00:49:39.476 --> 00:49:44.690
The body was so decayed
that there wasn't any flesh on him.

836
00:49:44.773 --> 00:49:46.525
-That all went in the tarp.
-Mm-hmm.

837
00:49:47.234 --> 00:49:49.528
-[man] Like a blue…
-[Carrie] One of those blue tarps.

838
00:49:49.611 --> 00:49:51.822
-[man] A Home Depot tarp? Okay.
-[Carrie] Yeah.

839
00:49:51.905 --> 00:49:54.408
At that time he was in the garage.

840
00:49:55.826 --> 00:49:59.371
[Lyndon] They bought cadaver deodorizer.

841
00:49:59.454 --> 00:50:02.457
Tyvek suits. and masks.
and different things like that.

842
00:50:02.541 --> 00:50:06.753
That's what somebody who would be dealing
with cadavers would need. right?

843
00:50:06.837 --> 00:50:09.673
The police even came
when he was still there.

844
00:50:11.008 --> 00:50:13.260
They stood in front of the body.

845
00:50:15.595 --> 00:50:17.556
The night that the police were there.

846
00:50:18.181 --> 00:50:21.518
I took him to my house in Beverly Glen.

847
00:50:28.316 --> 00:50:33.947
[Bella] One night in particular.
the noises were next level.

848
00:50:34.031 --> 00:50:41.038
It was totally a different scenario
than previous nights.

849
00:50:41.121 --> 00:50:42.789
[steady thumping]

850
00:50:42.873 --> 00:50:44.708
[Ashley] I didn't know what I was hearing.

851
00:50:44.791 --> 00:50:50.005
I would say it kind of just sounded like
a thumping noise where you drop furniture.

852
00:50:50.088 --> 00:50:51.840
It kind of sounded like that.

853
00:50:53.341 --> 00:50:56.178
[Bella] I heard voices.
I heard them talking.

854
00:50:57.220 --> 00:51:00.849
It seemed like they were carrying things.
heavy. in and out of the building.

855
00:51:01.975 --> 00:51:06.063
[Carrie] And then from there. uh.
we moved him up to my rooftop balcony

856
00:51:06.605 --> 00:51:08.940
because my neighbors
could see in the back patio.

857
00:51:09.024 --> 00:51:12.152
It was either that or the next day
we made a trip to Home Depot

858
00:51:13.361 --> 00:51:15.197
to buy acid and lye.

859
00:51:15.989 --> 00:51:18.784
[man] What sort of acid did you buy?
Do you recall?

860
00:51:18.867 --> 00:51:20.202
Um…

861
00:51:20.285 --> 00:51:22.913
Like stuff for pools. Chlorine.

862
00:51:22.996 --> 00:51:24.289
-[man] Chlorine? Okay.
-Yeah.

863
00:51:25.332 --> 00:51:29.294
[Carrie] I think we bought.
like. five gallons

864
00:51:29.377 --> 00:51:31.797
because we weren't sure
how much it was going to take.

865
00:51:31.880 --> 00:51:37.302
I believe we put the remains into
one of the blue barrels. the tall ones.

866
00:51:37.385 --> 00:51:38.720
filled with acid.

867
00:51:38.804 --> 00:51:39.638
[man] Okay.

868
00:51:39.721 --> 00:51:42.724
We took a bunch of drugs to deal with it.

869
00:51:43.850 --> 00:51:46.478
There's this infamous episode
in Breaking Bad

870
00:51:46.561 --> 00:51:48.146
where Walter and Jesse…

871
00:51:48.230 --> 00:51:49.981
[Jesse] Hey. Mr. White. it's me. pick up.

872
00:51:50.065 --> 00:51:53.235
[Lyndon] …try to dissolve
a body in a plastic tub.

873
00:51:54.736 --> 00:51:58.281
The acts that Caroline did
paralleled that.

874
00:51:59.741 --> 00:52:02.911
[Mark] Carrie and the assistant
purchased a big tub.

875
00:52:02.994 --> 00:52:07.415
acid. and lye. mixed it together.

876
00:52:07.499 --> 00:52:13.630
placed Charles' remains inside
this makeshift tub.

877
00:52:14.214 --> 00:52:17.801
and attempted to dissolve the body
to get rid of any evidence

878
00:52:17.884 --> 00:52:20.178
that may connect her with Charles.

879
00:52:20.262 --> 00:52:23.807
During this time.
apparently. it wasn't working.

880
00:52:23.890 --> 00:52:26.601
[man] How long did the remains
sit in the blue container?

881
00:52:26.685 --> 00:52:30.564
Probably for about a week
trying to get it to dissolve.

882
00:52:30.647 --> 00:52:32.482
[Lyndon] The chemicals were so strong.

883
00:52:32.566 --> 00:52:34.651
the tub started melting.

884
00:52:37.320 --> 00:52:39.739
[man] How did you get the blue bin
down to the patio?

885
00:52:39.823 --> 00:52:41.616
Or did you drain it from the third story?

886
00:52:41.700 --> 00:52:44.035
[Carrie] We drained it
from the third story all the way down.

887
00:52:44.119 --> 00:52:45.245
[man] All the way down? Hose?

888
00:52:45.328 --> 00:52:49.166
[Carrie] Yeah. hose. and we had a pump
that was pulling it out of the…

889
00:52:49.249 --> 00:52:51.126
-[man] Container.
-[Carrie] …container.

890
00:52:51.710 --> 00:52:54.754
The neighbor that lived across from Carrie

891
00:52:54.838 --> 00:52:59.176
had started to complain
about a really bad smell.

892
00:52:59.259 --> 00:53:03.513
And she said that
all the flowers and vegetation

893
00:53:03.597 --> 00:53:07.642
in the back of the building were dying.

894
00:53:08.894 --> 00:53:09.853
[liquid bubbling]

895
00:53:09.936 --> 00:53:12.647
[Carrie] The ligaments and stuff.
that dissolved.

896
00:53:12.731 --> 00:53:13.773
[man] Okay.

897
00:53:13.857 --> 00:53:15.734
[Carrie] So he was not
held together anymore.

898
00:53:15.817 --> 00:53:18.403
-[squelching]
-There was… The bones were just loose.

899
00:53:18.486 --> 00:53:20.947
but the majority of it did dissolve.

900
00:53:21.031 --> 00:53:22.782
The bones did not.

901
00:53:22.866 --> 00:53:27.287
At that point. Caroline decided
it's time to get him out of there.

902
00:53:28.079 --> 00:53:31.666
They took an axe and other tools.

903
00:53:31.750 --> 00:53:34.211
They started dismembering him further

904
00:53:34.294 --> 00:53:36.421
to try to make him unidentifiable.

905
00:53:36.504 --> 00:53:37.881
[loud sawing]

906
00:53:37.964 --> 00:53:39.549
[Ashley] What is she doing in her unit?

907
00:53:39.633 --> 00:53:43.428
Why is there so much banging that's
occurring at all hours of the night?

908
00:53:44.471 --> 00:53:47.974
[Bella] It sounded like a sawing sound.

909
00:53:48.058 --> 00:53:50.101
Something was going on.

910
00:53:50.185 --> 00:53:52.145
[Carrie] I pulled the teeth out
and crushed them.

911
00:53:52.229 --> 00:53:53.772
[man] How'd you pull them out?

912
00:53:53.855 --> 00:53:56.233
[Carrie] I'd just take them
out with my hand.

913
00:53:56.316 --> 00:53:58.735
The bones were just packaged up.

914
00:53:58.818 --> 00:54:00.403
We vacuum-sealed them.

915
00:54:01.488 --> 00:54:02.656
[man] The skull also?

916
00:54:02.739 --> 00:54:03.990
-Yeah.
-[man] Okay.

917
00:54:04.074 --> 00:54:07.619
And then we took them to San Francisco.

918
00:54:09.329 --> 00:54:12.624
[Lyndon] Caroline and her assistant
rented a sports car

919
00:54:12.707 --> 00:54:16.253
and traveled up north
to San Francisco Bay.

920
00:54:16.878 --> 00:54:19.422
where they had a friend
who lived on a boat.

921
00:54:21.591 --> 00:54:23.301
[Mark] They boarded the boat.

922
00:54:24.427 --> 00:54:25.929
went out into the bay.

923
00:54:27.639 --> 00:54:29.349
and disposed of his remains.

924
00:54:32.394 --> 00:54:34.396
And then they got on a private jet

925
00:54:35.313 --> 00:54:36.523
and flew back home.

926
00:54:37.357 --> 00:54:38.942
[man] You need another tissue?

927
00:54:39.025 --> 00:54:40.860
-Yeah. [sniffling]
-[man] All right.

928
00:54:40.944 --> 00:54:42.821
[Andrew] One of
the most frightening things

929
00:54:42.904 --> 00:54:46.366
that we found from the search warrant

930
00:54:46.449 --> 00:54:50.996
was that Caroline Herrling
had spreadsheets

931
00:54:51.079 --> 00:54:54.457
that listed deceased persons.

932
00:54:54.958 --> 00:54:56.918
their property holdings.

933
00:54:57.002 --> 00:54:59.045
and their heirs.

934
00:54:59.129 --> 00:55:05.760
So it appeared that she was trying
to use the Charles Wilding fraud

935
00:55:05.844 --> 00:55:08.430
as a template going forward

936
00:55:08.513 --> 00:55:12.559
to find other wealthy homeowners

937
00:55:12.642 --> 00:55:15.895
who wouldn't have anyone to protect them

938
00:55:15.979 --> 00:55:19.274
if she sought to steal their properties.

939
00:55:20.775 --> 00:55:23.820
[Lyndon] If the body of Charles
had been discovered.

940
00:55:23.903 --> 00:55:25.780
it would have foiled their plans.

941
00:55:26.448 --> 00:55:30.660
The actions she did
showed a complete callousness.

942
00:55:30.744 --> 00:55:34.831
almost a psychopathic-type personality

943
00:55:34.914 --> 00:55:38.043
to not care and not even be fazed

944
00:55:38.126 --> 00:55:40.920
by having to melt a body or chop it.

945
00:55:41.004 --> 00:55:46.551
It was just an item to do
to succeed in her fraud.

946
00:55:47.052 --> 00:55:49.721
KCAL News Assignment Editor
Mike Rogers is here.

947
00:55:49.804 --> 00:55:52.724
He's got details of a disturbing case.

948
00:55:52.807 --> 00:55:53.767
Yeah. Pat and Juan…

949
00:55:53.850 --> 00:55:59.064
I'm laying in bed. and the news pops on.
and it's just a picture of Carrie.

950
00:55:59.147 --> 00:56:01.191
[Mike] Allegedly.
there's the photo of the woman

951
00:56:01.274 --> 00:56:03.276
provided by the Department of Justice.

952
00:56:03.360 --> 00:56:08.615
they say would target elderly and disabled
and vulnerable people in the community.

953
00:56:08.698 --> 00:56:11.409
They tried to dispose
of the body in chemicals

954
00:56:11.493 --> 00:56:13.161
at her West Los Angeles apartment.

955
00:56:13.244 --> 00:56:16.956
It just brought me
to a moment of just shock.

956
00:56:19.751 --> 00:56:25.340
[Andrew] The conspirators themselves
called this a perfect crime.

957
00:56:26.174 --> 00:56:28.843
Charles Wilding was dead.

958
00:56:28.927 --> 00:56:31.763
and he didn't have any heirs.

959
00:56:31.846 --> 00:56:37.477
But for the good efforts of his neighbors.

960
00:56:37.560 --> 00:56:43.066
this fraud would probably never have
come to the attention of the authorities.

961
00:56:43.149 --> 00:56:46.820
and Ms. Herrling and her co-conspirators

962
00:56:46.903 --> 00:56:50.657
would have gotten away
with several million dollars.

963
00:57:01.459 --> 00:57:05.839
[Andrew] Caroline Herrling
was sentenced to 20 years in prison.

964
00:57:05.922 --> 00:57:08.466
which is the statutory maximum

965
00:57:08.550 --> 00:57:11.970
for wire fraud
and conspiracy to commit it.

966
00:57:12.053 --> 00:57:15.557
Anybody who is convicted of a conspiracy

967
00:57:15.640 --> 00:57:21.354
can be held accountable to all the crimes
that occurred within it.

968
00:57:21.438 --> 00:57:22.981
and she was.

969
00:57:23.064 --> 00:57:25.066
[pensive music playing]

970
00:57:37.829 --> 00:57:41.416
[Bella] I couldn't believe that
I was only 50 feet away

971
00:57:41.499 --> 00:57:43.626
from her chopping up a body.

972
00:57:44.836 --> 00:57:47.755
I never in a million years
thought Carrie would be capable

973
00:57:47.839 --> 00:57:50.216
of all the things she did.

974
00:57:51.301 --> 00:57:55.513
I had just assumed
she was a normal meth addict.

975
00:57:57.557 --> 00:58:00.101
In hindsight. now I realize that

976
00:58:00.185 --> 00:58:03.021
you never really know
who your neighbors are.

977
00:58:07.650 --> 00:58:10.069
[dramatic upbeat theme music playing]

977
00:58:11.305 --> 00:59:11.290
Press play. Subtitles appear.
